The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Good Morning

 Hello It's Monday, September 12, 2005

 Screen amp; stage

 The Hand of Fate and Blues ? the screen and theatre adaptations, respectively, of Katherine Mansfield?s The Fly, followed by a discussion, at Oxford Bookstore, 6.30 pm.

 Discussion

 A panel discussion on ?Public Relations: Key to Unlocking Myriad Horizons? at Bengal Club, 6 pm.

 A seminar on various facets of Bengali cinema at Nandan II, 6.30 pm. Rituparno Ghosh will talk on the language of cinema.

 Interface

 An interface with Kiran Bedi, organised by Ladies Study Group, at The Park, 3 pm.

 Theatre

 Khwabnama, directed by Kishore Sengupta, will be staged by Kalyani Natya Charcha Kendra, at Academy of Fine Arts, 6.30 pm.

 Soiree

 Bengali modern songs by Debosrita Basu at Swabhumi, 6 pm.

 A session of songs and poems at Sisir Mancha, 6 pm.

 Exhibition

 Art in Life, an exhibition of art items, decor, textiles, ready-to-wear, jewellery and books, at CIMA Gallery, 11 am to 8 pm.

 Saris, yardage, dupattas and stoles on view at Tvastr, Swabhumi, noon to 8 pm.

 An exhibition of photographs of poets at Gaganendra Pradarshashala, 2 pm to 8 pm.




